text:
English Kills: A view of the north bank as seen from the Metropolitan Ave. Bridge, showing the coal pockets of the Rosoff Coal and Fuel Corp. Beyond same is a large fuel tank, which would be on about Varick Ave., providing the latter continued. This set (panoramic) consists of two views.

October 29, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
title: English Kills - Brooklyn - North bank - [Rosoff Coal and Fuel Corporation.]
